    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="muted">
      Effective date: 2025-12-16 · This policy is intended to be comprehensive and describe how data is collected, used, stored, protected, shared, and deleted.  [oai_citation:11‡Amazon Developer Documentation](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/website-guidelines)
    </p>

    <div class="box">
      <p style="margin:0;">
        <strong>Privacy contact:</strong> <a href="mailto:privacy@margynx.com">privacy@margynx.com</a><br/>
        <strong>Support contact:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@margynx.com">support@margynx.com</a>
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>1) Who we are</h2>
    <p>
      Margynx provides “Agentix Seller Cockpit”, an analytics and performance optimization service for Amazon Selling Partners.
      This policy applies to our website (margynx.com) and our service.
    </p>

    <h2>2) Data we collect and access</h2>
    <p>
      We may process the following categories of information, depending on what a seller authorizes:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Account and service data:</strong> user email, organization name, configuration settings.</li>
      <li><strong>Seller-authorized Amazon data:</strong> operational and performance data accessed via Selling Partner API roles/endpoints the seller authorizes (e.g., reports, listings, sales performance, advertising-related signals where applicable, and brand analytics role data where authorized).</li>
      <li><strong>Website data:</strong> basic analytics logs (e.g., IP, user agent) for security and performance monitoring.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3) How we collect data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Seller authorization:</strong> sellers explicitly grant access via Amazon’s authorization workflow (OAuth/LWA-based flows).</li>
      <li><strong>Direct input:</strong> configuration values and optional business inputs provided by the seller (e.g., cost-of-goods for profitability modeling).</li>
      <li><strong>Automatic collection:</strong> limited website logs for security and troubleshooting.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4) How we use data</h2>
    <p>We use data only to operate and improve the service requested by the seller, including:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Generating dashboards, trend analysis, explanations, and recommendations.</li>
      <li>Detecting anomalies and producing alerts.</li>
      <li>Providing customer support and troubleshooting.</li>
      <li>Security monitoring and abuse prevention.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5) How we store and protect data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Encryption:</strong> data is protected in transit (HTTPS/TLS) and at rest where stored.</li>
      <li><strong>Access control:</strong> least-privilege access, role-based permissions, and operational audit practices.</li>
      <li><strong>Segregation:</strong> seller data is logically isolated per seller account.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6) Sharing and disclosure</h2>
    <p>
      We do not sell, rent, or disclose seller-authorized Amazon data to third parties for their independent use.
      We may use sub-processors (e.g., hosting providers) solely to operate the service; sub-processors must be bound to confidentiality
      and appropriate security obligations.
    </p>

    <h2>7) Data retention and deletion</h2>
    <p>
      We retain data only as long as needed to provide the service and meet legal/security obligations.
      If a seller revokes authorization or closes their account, we will delete or de-identify stored seller data within a reasonable timeframe,
      unless retention is required for legal compliance, security investigations, or dispute resolution.
    </p>

    <h2>8) Seller controls</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Sellers can revoke authorization through Amazon and/or request account closure.</li>
      <li>Sellers may request access, correction, or deletion where applicable under regional regulations.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>9) International and regional compliance</h2>
    <p>
      We aim to comply with applicable regional privacy regulations and Amazon’s Data Protection Policy requirements for SP-API
      applications and service providers.  [oai_citation:12‡Amazon Developer Documentation](https://developer-docs.amazon.com/sp-api/docs/website-guidelines)
    </p>

    <h2>10) Updates to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this policy from time to time. We will revise the effective date above when changes are made.
    </p>

    <footer>
